<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dannig</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">To my surprise I was dubious to Thurgadin, but no one would sell to me, saying:<P>"I don't talk to Dark Elves, much less sell to them!"<P>Yet I con dubious.<P>My question is this:<P>Is this a permanent thing or do I need to kill a few giants to get better faction?  <P>If I cannot ever sell there, then I will just go work on giant faction.<P>thanks<P>Dannig<P>------------------<BR>Dannig   52 Cleric<BR>Dark Elf <BR>Dark Asylum<BR>http://personal.pitnet.net/asylum/<BR>Xegony</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Pzar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hmmm...<BR>I might be mistaken but isn't it always so that you can't buy/sell when you are dubious. As far as I recall you have to be higher but again I might be wrong.<P>But as far as I know everyone should be able to be ok in Thurg/Kael/SS with some faction work.<P>Pzar.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Kayleigh</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wow I'm surprised. I thought everyone started at "apprehensive" with them. Merchants will sell to you at apprehensive, but not at dubious.<P>You can raise this faction - just go whack some giants.  If you can get into a Kael arena group, you can send your faction soaring very easily.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wisecleric</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sounds like you took a faction hit against the coldain somewhere. You might have just been passing by someone killing dwarves, it happens. But with just one or two faction hits, all it takes is to hit a few giants being killed and you should be good to go. </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeardly</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Get behind the merchant and hide (you are a DE after all).  This will take your faction to indifferent.  You should be able to sell then.<P>Note: I believe this can be done.  It works with sneak, and I'm pretty sure it does with hide as well.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Caleal</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Yeardly:<BR><B>Get behind the merchant and hide (you are a DE after all).  This will take your faction to indifferent.  You should be able to sell then.<P>Note: I believe this can be done.  It works with sneak, and I'm pretty sure it does with hide as well.</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Hide drops when you open the merchant screen.<P><P>------------------<BR>Caleal P`Terak<BR>BATTLE CLERIC of Innoruuk<BR>Cazic-Thule server<BR>Officer, Shadowed Soul</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">At dubious, they wont talk to you. Or they will, but it's usually stuff like <P>"Oh yes, I think I have something for you. The EXIT. Now use it."<P>Get to apprehensive and you can sell. But your prices will suck. I actually do my Velious buying and selling in Kael because I am Amiable to Dwarves but Ally to Storm Giants. (Indifferent to Frost Giants and Dubious to King Tormax)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dannig</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I just tried the hide thing, it did not work   <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/frown.gif">  Thanks for the idead though.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">tailchaser</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My agnostic barbarian rogue's Thurgadin faction does not change at all when I go from Barbarian to Dark Elf forms, so it's nothing to do with you being a Dark Elf.<P>Very possibly might have something to do with worshipping Innoruuk, tho.<P>If you're wanting to make Thurgadin your home base in Velious, then just grab a warrior, go into the Great Divide, and start killing Drakkel Dire Wolves and Frost Giant Scouts, it won't take long.  Save the giant heads and toes for additional faction via quests.<P>If you're planning to align with giants anyway, and the Coldain are already Dubious to begin with...heck, just start the slaughter.  ;p</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bennan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">A guy I know that does the Gate quests etc is a Dark Elf Necromancer, so you should be right.<P>You will just have to kill Giants and Wolfs to get your faction up.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Galavant</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Race and religion and all that do make a difference in Thurgadin.<P>Most people start out apprehensive. If you're normally an evil type, expect to be dubious. Followers of Rallos Zek are probably dubious if not KOS in Thurgadin.<P>On the other hand, followers of Rallos Zek aren't KOS to the giants. Neither are ogres apparently. It's something to keep in mind. I wonder how the few followers of Veeshan are received by the dragons...<P>Me, I'm a DWARF cleric of BRELL. I started out indifferent in Thurgadin. It took me only a very few giant kills to get to amiable.<P>------------------<BR>Galavant Greenlabel<BR>http://www.geocities.com/mirthandmayhem<BR>Rathe Server<P>"Judge not by size, but rather by spirit."</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Jaldarith</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">You took a Dwarf faction hit Dannig, maybe without you knowing it, maybe you just helped kill something with coldain faction attatched to it.  I'm a Dark Elf Cleric that worships Inny, and I started out apprehensive.  No reason some other Cleric with the same diety should be dubious at first.<P>Just kill a couple Drakkel Dire Wolves or Frost giant scouts, or something with a warrior friend.  10 or so faction hits and you'll be back to apprehensive.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
